### Step 7 — Weekly new content summary

Append to `~/Seo-workflow-mindtalk/mindtalk-setup/logs/new-content-[WEEK-START].txt`:
- Keywords selected this week with their type and search volume
- Running count of new content briefs created this month
- Any keywords reclassified from new content → content refresh

## Important rules

- Maximum 20 new content briefs per week
- New content briefs are prefixed with "NEW-" in the filename to distinguish 
  from refresh briefs
- Never edit existing MDX files in this task
- Clinical accuracy matters: for illness/treatment pages, do not suggest 
  medical claims without direction to cite a source
- All new blog content must be relevant to people seeking mental health support — 
  do not suggest off-topic blog ideas
- If a keyword is better served by refreshing an existing page (intent match), 
  reclassify it and route to the refresh workflow rather than creating a new page

